1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:09,660
Room full of noise, hands in the air,

2
00:00:09,810 --> 00:00:14,469
Everybody racing to get somewhere.

3
00:00:14,619 --> 00:00:19,279
I’m in the back, clicking a fidget cube,

4
00:00:19,429 --> 00:00:24,089
Watching the whole thing come unglued.

5
00:00:24,239 --> 00:00:28,899
They say I’m quiet, they say I wait,

6
00:00:29,049 --> 00:00:33,708
Like I’m late to some invisible gate.

7
00:00:33,858 --> 00:00:38,518
But I’m just listening, stacking the
truth,

8
00:00:38,668 --> 00:00:43,328
Letting it age, letting it proof.

9
00:00:43,478 --> 00:00:48,138
I don’t burn words just to fill the air,

10
00:00:48,288 --> 00:00:52,947
I don’t spend them like I don’t care.

11
00:00:53,097 --> 00:00:57,757
When Lily talks, the room goes still,

12
00:00:57,907 --> 00:01:02,567
Chairs stop scraping, even the ticking
chills.

13
00:01:02,717 --> 00:01:07,376
I don’t say much, but when I do,

14
00:01:07,526 --> 00:01:12,186
Every head nods like they always knew.

15
00:01:12,336 --> 00:01:16,996
When Lily talks, you hear it twice,

16
00:01:17,146 --> 00:01:21,806
Once in the sound, once in the silence.

17
00:01:21,956 --> 00:01:26,615
Teachers say, “her voice matters,”

18
00:01:26,765 --> 00:01:31,425
Friends listen close when she speaks, not
scattered.

19
00:01:31,575 --> 00:01:36,235
I take my time, I read the room,

20
00:01:36,385 --> 00:01:41,045
I don’t rush daylight, I don’t chase noon.

21
00:01:41,195 --> 00:01:45,854
I work alone, I work just fine,

22
00:01:46,004 --> 00:01:50,664
I’ll ask for help when the question’s
mine.

23
00:01:50,814 --> 00:01:55,474
I don’t raise hands just to be seen,

24
00:01:55,624 --> 00:02:00,284
I speak when the thought is sharp and
clean.

25
00:02:00,434 --> 00:02:05,093
When Lily talks, people lean in,

26
00:02:05,243 --> 00:02:09,903
Like they missed the start and this is the
win.

27
00:02:10,053 --> 00:02:14,713
Not loud, not fast, not dressed to
impress,

28
00:02:14,863 --> 00:02:19,522
Just one clear sentence, nothing less.

29
00:02:19,672 --> 00:02:24,332
Attention isn’t noise or size,

30
00:02:24,482 --> 00:02:29,142
It’s knowing when to open your mouth and
why.

31
00:02:29,292 --> 00:02:33,952
You can shout all day, you can sell the
room,

32
00:02:34,102 --> 00:02:38,761
But still miss the moment that lands the
boom.

33
00:02:38,911 --> 00:02:43,571
When Lily talks, the room remembers,

34
00:02:43,721 --> 00:02:48,381
Lunchroom, classroom, late November.

35
00:02:48,531 --> 00:02:53,191
I don’t chase echoes, I don’t pursue,

36
00:02:53,341 --> 00:02:58,000
I talk when it’s true — and then it’s
true.

37
00:02:58,150 --> 00:03:02,810
I’ve been listening the whole damn time.
